mo}}\n[[Category:1909 births]]\n[[Category:1973 deaths]]\n[[Category:Italian male cyclists]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Varese]]\n", "text_old": "{{Unreferenced|date=June 2019|bot=noref (GreenC bot)}}\n{{for|the footballer|Remo Bertoni (footballer)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{MedalTableTop}}\n{{MedalCountry|{{flagcountry|ITA|1861}}}}\n{{MedalSport| Men's [[road bicycle racing]] }}\n{{MedalCompetition|World Championships}}\n{{MedalSilver |[[1929 UCI Road World Championships|1929 Z\u00fcrich]]|Amateur's Road Race}}\n{{MedalSilver |[[1932 UCI Road World Championships|1932 Rome]]|Elite Men's Road Race}}\n{{MedalBottom}}\n[[File:Remo Bertoni.jpg|thumb|Remo Bertoni]]\n'''Remo Bertoni''' (21 June 1909 \u2013 18 September 1973) was an [[Italy|Italian]] professional [[road bicycle racer]].\n\nBertoni was born in [[Varese]].  He is best known for his silver medal in the Elite race of the [[1932 UCI Road World Championships]].  He died, aged 64, in [[Milan]].\n\n== Palmares ==\n{{Palmares start}}\n;1929 - Amateur & Legnano\n: {{ITA}} Independent Road Race Champion\n: {{sica}} World Amateur Road Race Championship\n;1930 - Legnano\n;1931 - Legnano\n: 1st, [[GP Bendoni]]\n: 1st, [[GP Masnego]]\n: 1st, Stages 2 & 3, [[Giro di Campania]]\n;1932 - Legnano, Gloria\n: 1st, [[Treviso-Monte Grappa]]\n: {{sica}} World Road Race Championship\n: 2nd, National Road Race Championship\n: 3rd, [[1932 Giro d'Italia|Giro d'Italia]]\n:: Winner Stage 11\n: 3rd, [[Giro di Lombardia]]\n;1933 - Bianchi\n: 1st, [[Pistoia-Prunetta]]\n: 2nd, National Road Race Championship\n: 19th, [[1933 Giro d'Italia|Giro d'Italia]]\n;1934 - Legnano\n: 1st, [[Castellanza-Macugnaga]]\n: 1st, [[Cittiglio-Leffe]]\n: 6th, [[1934 Giro d'Italia|Giro d'Italia]]\n::Winner [[Mountains classification in the Giro d'Italia|mountains classification]]\n;1935 - Legnano\n: 6th, [[1935 Giro d'Italia|Giro d'Italia]]\n;1936 - Il Littorale\n;1937 - Il Littorale, Urago\n;1938\n: 1st, [[Coppa Victoria]]\n;1939\n: {{ITA}} C